question.en:
Consider the following code structure and determine the pattern used:
```js
class PaymentProcessor {
  processVisa(payment) { /* Visa logic */ }
  processMasterCard(payment) { /* MasterCard logic */ }
  processPayPal(payment) { /* PayPal logic */ }
  process(type, payment) {
    switch(type) {
      case 'visa': return this.processVisa(payment);
      case 'mastercard': return this.processMasterCard(payment);
      case 'paypal': return this.processPayPal(payment);
    }
  }
}
```
Which refactoring would best apply Factory vs Abstract Factory pattern here?

