question.en:
Analyze this code and predict the output:
```js
class PaymentContext {
  constructor(strategy) { this.strategy = strategy; }
  setStrategy(strategy) { this.strategy = strategy; }
  pay(amount) { return this.strategy.execute(amount); }
}

class CreditCardStrategy { execute(amount) { return `Pay ${amount} via CC`; } }
class BitcoinStrategy { execute(amount) { return `Pay ${amount} via BTC`; } }

const context = new PaymentContext(new CreditCardStrategy());
console.log(context.pay(100));
context.setStrategy(new BitcoinStrategy());
console.log(context.pay(100));
```
What pattern is demonstrated and why is it fundamentally different from State?

